 A/(I\cap J) \cong A/I\times A/J 
\phi :A \rightarrow A/I\times  A/J 
ker(\phi)=I\cap J
I + J = A
I\cap J=IJ 
I + J = 1\,\Rightarrow\, i + j = 1\,
\,i\in I,\, j\in J\,
\,i\equiv 0\pmod{I},\ i\equiv 1\pmod{J}\,
\,\phi(i) = (0,1).\,
\,\phi(j) = (1,0).\,
\phi\,
\,{\rm Im}\,\phi = A/I\times A/J,\,
\qquad x := j_1\cdots j_n = (1-i_1)\cdot (1-i_n)\equiv 1^n\equiv 1\pmod{I},\,
\ x\equiv 0\pmod {J_k}
